15 2. A comprehensive physical examination;
16 3. Laboratory services;
17 4. Photo documentation;
18 5. Follow-up evaluation; or
19 6. A mental health screening to determine the impact of the alleged abuse
20 on the mental health status of the child and the need for mental health
21 services;
22 (d) "Physician" has the same meaning as in KRS 311.550; and
23 (e) "Sexual assault nurse examiner" has the same meaning as in KRS 314.011.
24 (2) The Cabinet for Health and Family Services and any managed care organization or
25 other entity with which[whom] the Department for Medicaid Services contracts for
26 the delivery of Medicaid services shall provide Medicaid reimbursement for a child
27 medical evaluation provided by a licensed physician, advanced practice registered
